1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:36,020
[To Ship Someone]

3
00:01:36,140 --> 00:01:39,000
[Episode 2]

4
00:01:54,740 --> 00:01:55,800
The power went out.

5
00:02:03,900 --> 00:02:05,020
It must be fake!

6
00:02:06,300 --> 00:02:08,139
What was that?

7
00:02:08,259 --> 00:02:09,300
What on earth

8
00:02:09,979 --> 00:02:11,740
was that?

9
00:02:24,950 --> 00:02:27,640
[Yu Le: I'll go to the convenience store to buy some ice. We'll put it on your wound after going home…]

10
00:02:40,820 --> 00:02:43,600
[Sun Xitian took out sunglasses from her bag and gave them to Yu Le…]

11
00:02:43,940 --> 00:02:45,740
Except for me,

12
00:02:46,260 --> 00:02:48,320
everything else is exactly the same.

13
00:02:49,260 --> 00:02:50,190
Was that a dream?

14
00:02:50,940 --> 00:02:52,340
I thought a lot about it during the day

15
00:02:52,340 --> 00:02:54,000
so I dreamed about it at night?

16
00:02:56,500 --> 00:02:57,030
Who's it?

17
00:02:57,220 --> 00:02:59,579
Song Yanqi, open the door!

18
00:02:59,860 --> 00:03:01,420
Song Yanqi.

19
00:03:01,780 --> 00:03:03,340
Song Yanqi!

20
00:03:04,540 --> 00:03:05,540
Song Yanqi!

21
00:03:05,580 --> 00:03:07,060
Open the door!

22
00:03:08,580 --> 00:03:09,460
Song Yanqi!

23
00:03:09,660 --> 00:03:10,500
Song Yanqi!

24
00:03:11,140 --> 00:03:13,500
You know I'm afraid of thunder.

25
00:03:13,660 --> 00:03:15,140
-How could you lock your door? -I...

26
00:03:15,140 --> 00:03:16,780
Sorry. I just fell asleep.

27
00:03:37,820 --> 00:03:38,860
Are you okay now?

28
00:03:41,980 --> 00:03:42,940
In the future,

29
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:45,980
you can only lock your door

30
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:47,700
when you're in bed with a man.

31
00:03:48,060 --> 00:03:48,940
At other times,

32
00:03:49,380 --> 00:03:50,820
don't you dare lock your door!

33
00:03:50,820 --> 00:03:53,480
Xingxing, what nonsense are you talking about?

34
00:03:55,420 --> 00:03:56,210
Xingxing.

35
00:03:56,860 --> 00:03:59,180
Let me tell you something unbelievable.

36
00:03:59,380 --> 00:03:59,940
Okay.

37
00:04:00,380 --> 00:04:01,900
I suspect

38
00:04:02,340 --> 00:04:04,270
I traveled into the novel just now.

39
00:04:04,540 --> 00:04:06,660
I saw Yu Le and Ye Xining.

40
00:04:09,260 --> 00:04:10,690
Do you think you're in a novel?

41
00:04:10,690 --> 00:04:11,890
That was just a dream.

42
00:04:12,700 --> 00:04:14,030
You're so imaginative.

43
00:04:14,340 --> 00:04:15,980
Why don't you write a novel yourself?

44
00:04:15,980 --> 00:04:17,579
Maybe you can become famous.

45
00:04:18,380 --> 00:04:19,579
You don't believe me?

46
00:04:20,380 --> 00:04:21,110
Give me a pen.

47
00:04:21,410 --> 00:04:23,540
No twist of fate!

48
00:04:23,780 --> 00:04:25,340
My characters will fall in love in the first chapter,

49
00:04:25,340 --> 00:04:26,540
get married in the tenth chapter,

50
00:04:26,540 --> 00:04:27,460
and have a baby in the 20th chapter.

51
00:04:27,460 --> 00:04:28,540
Two children in three years and three in five.

52
00:04:28,540 --> 00:04:29,580
They'll help raise the birth rate

53
00:04:29,580 --> 00:04:30,340
and participate in

54
00:04:30,340 --> 00:04:31,380
parent and child programs

55
00:04:31,380 --> 00:04:32,840
to make everyone envious.

56
00:04:33,460 --> 00:04:36,860
Reading too many novels has made you insane.

57
00:04:38,340 --> 00:04:39,670
I hope that was the case.

58
00:04:40,260 --> 00:04:42,220
If I can't get the copyright of the novel,

59
00:04:42,220 --> 00:04:43,540
I'll get sacked.

60
00:04:46,340 --> 00:04:47,020
Buck up.

61
00:04:47,900 --> 00:04:49,960
Don't let my money fly out the window.

62
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:54,520
I'm going to sleep.

63
00:04:54,780 --> 00:04:55,980
Wait. You're going to sleep here?

64
00:04:55,980 --> 00:04:56,420
Yes.

65
00:04:57,020 --> 00:04:58,420
You're an adult now.

66
00:04:58,460 --> 00:05:00,220
Grow up!

67
00:05:00,340 --> 00:05:01,220
I'm already asleep.

68
00:05:01,220 --> 00:05:02,140
Go back.

69
00:05:08,140 --> 00:05:10,020
I saw you push my son.

70
00:05:10,460 --> 00:05:12,220
See? His hand got grazed.

71
00:05:12,380 --> 00:05:13,380
I didn't push him.

72
00:05:13,460 --> 00:05:14,780
He bumped into me and fell.

73
00:05:14,780 --> 00:05:16,140
Ask him if you don't believe me.

74
00:05:16,140 --> 00:05:17,890
I saw you push him.

75
00:05:18,100 --> 00:05:19,430
I demand compensation.

76
00:05:21,140 --> 00:05:21,900
Wait.

77
00:05:22,020 --> 00:05:23,020
You want to walk away?

78
00:05:23,020 --> 00:05:23,660
No way!

79
00:05:25,340 --> 00:05:26,060
Madam,

80
00:05:26,100 --> 00:05:27,540
is there any misunderstanding?

81
00:05:27,540 --> 00:05:28,780
I know him.

82
00:05:29,260 --> 00:05:30,700
He wouldn't mess with a little boy.

83
00:05:30,700 --> 00:05:31,580
Who are you?

84
00:05:31,780 --> 00:05:33,180
Why should I believe you?

85
00:05:34,140 --> 00:05:34,780
Listen.

86
00:05:34,820 --> 00:05:36,020
You must pay me today.

87
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:37,260
According to your logic,

88
00:05:37,260 --> 00:05:38,540
you might be lying too.

89
00:05:38,580 --> 00:05:39,900
Why should I believe you?

90
00:05:39,900 --> 00:05:41,810
I suspect that you're blackmailing him.

91
00:05:41,810 --> 00:05:43,020
That's nonsense!

92
00:05:43,090 --> 00:05:44,550
I'm not blackmailing him!

93
00:05:47,380 --> 00:05:48,130
Kid,

94
00:05:48,540 --> 00:05:49,670
take a careful look.

95
00:05:49,810 --> 00:05:51,340
Did this guy push you?

96
00:05:51,659 --> 00:05:52,460
No.

97
00:05:52,580 --> 00:05:54,659
I bumped into him and fell.

98
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:56,580
He helped me up.

99
00:05:56,980 --> 00:05:58,020
What?

100
00:05:58,659 --> 00:05:59,140
Madam,

101
00:05:59,659 --> 00:06:01,570
perhaps you don't believe your own child either.

102
00:06:01,570 --> 00:06:02,370
But you have to

103
00:06:02,660 --> 00:06:04,790
believe the security footage, right?

104
00:06:05,580 --> 00:06:06,170
Fine.

105
00:06:07,900 --> 00:06:09,100
I'm out of luck today.

106
00:06:09,820 --> 00:06:10,350
Let's go.

107
00:06:12,780 --> 00:06:13,730
Poor boy.

108
00:06:13,780 --> 00:06:15,980
-Thank you. -His mother is a nightmare.

109
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:19,460
Mr. Ji.

110
00:06:20,540 --> 00:06:22,220
I'm here today for…

111
00:06:22,220 --> 00:06:23,860
I apologize for

112
00:06:24,020 --> 00:06:25,780
taking you as a thief yesterday.

113
00:06:25,780 --> 00:06:27,460
It feels bad to be misunderstood, right?

114
00:06:27,460 --> 00:06:28,720
But it doesn't matter.

115
00:06:29,580 --> 00:06:30,780
As for the copyright,

116
00:06:31,020 --> 00:06:32,280
I won't change my mind.

117
00:06:33,700 --> 00:06:35,820
I never expected to convince you easily.

118
00:06:35,820 --> 00:06:37,340
I won't give up.

119
00:06:37,690 --> 00:06:39,220
No matter how many times you come to me,

120
00:06:39,220 --> 00:06:40,540
my answer is the same.

121
00:06:59,780 --> 00:07:00,840
The guy with a mask?

122
00:07:02,540 --> 00:07:03,700
It was you

123
00:07:03,980 --> 00:07:05,710
at the bus stop that day, right?

124
00:07:07,940 --> 00:07:08,700
What a surprise.

125
00:07:08,700 --> 00:07:09,810
It turns out

126
00:07:10,020 --> 00:07:10,980
that we've met before.

127
00:07:10,980 --> 00:07:12,100
I live nearby.

128
00:07:12,220 --> 00:07:13,060
We'll

129
00:07:13,220 --> 00:07:14,740
meet a lot in the future.

130
00:07:16,580 --> 00:07:17,580
I'll say it again.

131
00:07:17,620 --> 00:07:18,500
I won't sell the copyright.

132
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:20,180
Please leave me alone.

133
00:07:23,140 --> 00:07:24,260
Why don't you let me tell you

134
00:07:24,260 --> 00:07:25,920
what we've got to offer first?

135
00:07:26,380 --> 00:07:27,700
No matter what you can offer,

136
00:07:27,700 --> 00:07:28,830
I'm not interested.

137
00:07:28,900 --> 00:07:29,540
Why?

138
00:07:30,900 --> 00:07:33,659
So many good novels have been adapted into rubbish.

139
00:07:33,659 --> 00:07:34,620
The recreation of the script

140
00:07:34,620 --> 00:07:35,740
will be under the pressure from many parties.

141
00:07:35,740 --> 00:07:37,100
The outcome will be nothing like the original work.

142
00:07:37,100 --> 00:07:38,260
So I won't sell my novel.

143
00:07:38,260 --> 00:07:39,020
I promise

144
00:07:39,020 --> 00:07:40,620
that we won't do big changes.

145
00:07:41,659 --> 00:07:42,570
How can you be so sure?

146
00:07:42,570 --> 00:07:43,100
I…

147
00:07:43,980 --> 00:07:44,780
I…

148
00:07:45,580 --> 00:07:46,060
I…

149
00:07:46,770 --> 00:07:47,220
I…

150
00:07:50,580 --> 00:07:51,780
How can I be so sure?

151
00:07:52,780 --> 00:07:54,140
How could a warm-blooded human

152
00:07:54,140 --> 00:07:55,860
say something so cold?

153
00:08:02,380 --> 00:08:03,780
Have you seen the trending topics on Weibo?

154
00:08:03,780 --> 00:08:06,020
Big production companies are laying off employees again.

155
00:08:06,020 --> 00:08:07,280
The economy is bad now.

156
00:08:07,340 --> 00:08:08,740
Maybe the next one getting sacked

157
00:08:08,740 --> 00:08:09,500
will be you.

158
00:08:09,580 --> 00:08:10,700
It can't be me!

159
00:08:11,220 --> 00:08:11,950
Don't worry.

160
00:08:12,260 --> 00:08:13,920
I'll get sacked before you do.

161
00:08:24,100 --> 00:08:24,760
Song Yanqi.

162
00:08:24,780 --> 00:08:25,260
Mr. Jia.

163
00:08:25,700 --> 00:08:27,140
I went to the platform today.

164
00:08:27,140 --> 00:08:28,770
They think highly of Brighter Than Stars

165
00:08:28,770 --> 00:08:30,900
and have been paying attention to its author for a long time.

166
00:08:30,900 --> 00:08:31,340
So,

167
00:08:31,660 --> 00:08:33,789
get its copyright as soon as possible.

168
00:08:34,220 --> 00:08:34,820
Mr. Jia,

169
00:08:36,980 --> 00:08:38,460
the author refused to sell the copyright.

170
00:08:38,460 --> 00:08:39,020
Refuse?

171
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:40,059
Why?

172
00:08:40,820 --> 00:08:42,460
He's worried that we'd make too many changes to his work.

173
00:08:42,460 --> 00:08:44,820
Tell him that we respect the original work.

174
00:08:44,820 --> 00:08:46,350
You should know what to say!

175
00:08:46,740 --> 00:08:48,460
That's what I said, but he…

176
00:08:48,740 --> 00:08:50,820
No one would refuse a chance to make money.

177
00:08:50,820 --> 00:08:51,650
No one.

178
00:08:51,850 --> 00:08:53,700
He brushed you off with some lame excuse

179
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:54,560
and you gave up?

180
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:56,500
I didn't hire you to be a quitter!

181
00:08:58,980 --> 00:08:59,440
Mr. Jia.

182
00:09:02,740 --> 00:09:04,140
If Song Yanqi can't do it,

183
00:09:04,460 --> 00:09:05,520
let me give it a try.

184
00:09:05,860 --> 00:09:06,500
I can.

185
00:09:06,860 --> 00:09:07,920
Mr. Jia, I can do it.

186
00:09:10,220 --> 00:09:11,100
Just get it done.

187
00:09:11,100 --> 00:09:11,540
Okay.

188
00:09:15,300 --> 00:09:16,960
You can't handle that author.

189
00:09:17,100 --> 00:09:18,500
Don't waste your energy.

190
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:20,100
Why are you so sure

191
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:21,430
that you can handle him?

192
00:09:22,100 --> 00:09:22,860
I just can.

193
00:09:28,740 --> 00:09:30,620
No one would refuse a chance to make money.

194
00:09:30,620 --> 00:09:31,950
If it's not about money,

195
00:09:31,970 --> 00:09:32,980
it got to be about people.

196
00:09:32,980 --> 00:09:34,820
Qi must have done something wrong.

197
00:09:34,820 --> 00:09:36,100
I told you to comfort her,

198
00:09:36,100 --> 00:09:37,500
not to rub it in.

199
00:09:43,260 --> 00:09:45,280
[Ji Shu]

200
00:09:53,340 --> 00:09:54,100
Mr. Ji.

201
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:55,460
Are you free this afternoon?

202
00:09:55,460 --> 00:09:56,580
Yes.

203
00:09:57,220 --> 00:09:58,180
See you at Ink Bookstore

204
00:09:58,180 --> 00:09:59,420
at three.

205
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:01,460
No problem.

206
00:10:02,460 --> 00:10:03,100
Mr. Jia.

207
00:10:04,940 --> 00:10:06,340
Mr. Ji wants to meet me to discuss the copyright.

208
00:10:06,340 --> 00:10:07,140
I'm going out.

209
00:10:20,660 --> 00:10:21,900
I'm not late.

210
00:10:24,620 --> 00:10:25,940
He's early.

211
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:31,340
Sorry, Mr. Ji.

212
00:10:31,610 --> 00:10:32,340
Am I late?

213
00:10:35,220 --> 00:10:36,750
You're five minutes early.

214
00:10:40,010 --> 00:10:40,700
Mr. Ji,

215
00:10:40,380 --> 00:10:41,010
[Adaption Plan for Brighter Than Stars]

216
00:10:40,850 --> 00:10:42,420
this is the adaptation plan I wrote.

217
00:10:42,420 --> 00:10:43,460
If you have any objections,

218
00:10:43,460 --> 00:10:44,520
I'll revise it now.

219
00:10:45,220 --> 00:10:47,020
This is the copyright contract.

220
00:10:47,180 --> 00:10:49,180
This is the scriptwriter contract.

221
00:10:49,460 --> 00:10:51,220
Considering that you don't have much experience in adapting,

222
00:10:51,220 --> 00:10:53,100
here are some scriptwriters we signed.

223
00:10:53,100 --> 00:10:53,580
Take a look.

224
00:10:53,580 --> 00:10:55,420
Do you need someone to work with you?

225
00:10:55,420 --> 00:10:56,420
Don't get me wrong.

226
00:10:56,420 --> 00:10:57,820
You have the final say.

227
00:10:58,100 --> 00:11:00,260
What matters most is the copyright.

228
00:11:02,580 --> 00:11:03,860
Pen. Pen.

229
00:11:12,340 --> 00:11:13,260
Mr. Ji,

230
00:11:13,740 --> 00:11:15,420
we haven't signed the contract yet.

231
00:11:15,420 --> 00:11:16,620
It's so kind of you to give me a gift,

232
00:11:16,620 --> 00:11:17,220
but I think

233
00:11:17,340 --> 00:11:19,220
it's a bit too early.

234
00:11:21,460 --> 00:11:23,660
You took my parcel without permission.

235
00:11:23,860 --> 00:11:25,620
You have to be responsible for the damage.

236
00:11:25,620 --> 00:11:26,620
I didn't break it.

237
00:11:27,050 --> 00:11:29,450
The deliveryman said it wasn't him either.

238
00:11:29,820 --> 00:11:30,580
But he told me

239
00:11:30,700 --> 00:11:32,060
that you pretended to be my girlfriend

240
00:11:32,060 --> 00:11:33,520
and signed for my package.

241
00:11:33,980 --> 00:11:35,580
Sorry. I'll pay for it.

242
00:11:35,700 --> 00:11:36,630
How much is this?

243
00:11:36,740 --> 00:11:38,100
12,740 yuan.

244
00:11:38,980 --> 00:11:39,740
What?

245
00:11:40,180 --> 00:11:41,220
More than 10,000 yuan?

246
00:11:41,220 --> 00:11:42,350
This thing can't be…

247
00:11:46,860 --> 00:11:47,820
Mr. Ji.

248
00:11:48,100 --> 00:11:49,700
I don't have so much money.

249
00:11:50,060 --> 00:11:51,520
Can I pay in installments?

250
00:11:51,610 --> 00:11:52,940
I don't need your money.

251
00:11:56,980 --> 00:11:57,780
I just need you

252
00:11:57,940 --> 00:12:00,540
to order a set of teacups exactly like this one.

253
00:12:01,860 --> 00:12:02,380
Okay.

254
00:12:03,340 --> 00:12:05,420
I didn't mean to break it.

255
00:12:06,220 --> 00:12:07,660
You've said that.

256
00:12:09,980 --> 00:12:10,420
Well,

257
00:12:10,980 --> 00:12:11,620
if you

258
00:12:11,620 --> 00:12:12,610
sign the contract now,

259
00:12:12,610 --> 00:12:14,070
I'll have money to pay you.

260
00:12:14,700 --> 00:12:15,100
You…

261
00:12:26,700 --> 00:12:28,620
I didn't do it!

262
00:12:36,660 --> 00:12:39,180
12740.

263
00:12:39,860 --> 00:12:42,540
12740.

264
00:12:46,300 --> 00:12:50,120
[Even if there's nothing worth my love in this world, I'll never stop loving.]

265
00:12:54,220 --> 00:12:55,300
Hey, Xingxing.

266
00:12:55,380 --> 00:12:57,060
I'm so mad at Ji Shu.

267
00:12:57,380 --> 00:12:58,780
He said this story is not ideal

268
00:12:58,780 --> 00:13:00,300
and wants to end it in advance.

269
00:13:00,300 --> 00:13:01,730
He'll design a car accident

270
00:13:01,730 --> 00:13:03,540
where Sun Xitian gets hurt for saving Yu Le.

271
00:13:03,540 --> 00:13:05,300
Yu Le will take care of her afterward.

272
00:13:05,300 --> 00:13:06,540
The couple you love

273
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:08,360
will part ways.

274
00:13:08,420 --> 00:13:09,260
What?

275
00:13:10,540 --> 00:13:11,660
It's the 21st century.

276
00:13:11,660 --> 00:13:13,320
Can't he write something new?

277
00:13:13,660 --> 00:13:15,740
You're the editor. Stop him.

278
00:13:15,900 --> 00:13:17,260
I want to,

279
00:13:17,780 --> 00:13:19,510
but he wouldn't answer my calls

280
00:13:19,620 --> 00:13:20,950
or reply to my messages.

281
00:13:21,780 --> 00:13:23,060
This is the result of your negotiation?

282
00:13:23,060 --> 00:13:23,980
A bad ending?

283
00:13:24,140 --> 00:13:25,140
Song Yanqi, listen.

284
00:13:25,140 --> 00:13:26,530
If that story has a bad ending, you'll too!

285
00:13:26,530 --> 00:13:27,190
Song Yanqi!

286
00:13:27,740 --> 00:13:29,300
I told you that you can't handle it.

287
00:13:29,300 --> 00:13:30,420
Don't do things

288
00:13:30,420 --> 00:13:31,950
that you're not capable of.

289
00:13:33,820 --> 00:13:35,580
Xingxing, listen to me.

